He says the slogan and symbols are different from the Movement for Movement for Democratic Change (MDC) he was leading. Chamisa formed the new party following calls by his supporters to abandon the MDC. Citizens Coalition for Change (CCC) will be the party to watch come by elections in March and harmonized polls in 2023. During his announce on Monday, Chamisa said the CCC is not a rebranded MDC but a different entity. Chamisa took over the reins power from the late founder of MDC, Morgan Richard Tsvangirai, in February 2018. For full interview click audio below: --ChannelAfrica/John Cassim-- 